<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4773495>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 6. Identity plate of the Taxodium dubium whole-plant. a) foliage shoot, Castelnuovo Don Bosco, Piacenzian (from Bertini and Martinetto 2014). b) cone from Villafranca d’Asti – RDB Quarry, Piacenzian. c) remains of woody axes missing. d) seeds from the same site. e) remains of amenta missing. f) Taxodium-type pollen from Rio Maior (photo by M. Vieira, Portugal: Vieira et al. 2018), Piacenzian. g) reconstruction of the Taxodium dubium whole-plant based on line of evidence ISA (drawing L. Macaluso). Scale bar 10 mm for a, 1 mm for b, d and 20 µm for f." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4773495/files/figure.png" .

